Installation instructions

1. Make sure the following packages are installed:
    Clang (part of LLVM)
    libc++ (part of LLVM)
    X.Org X server
    Qt (including QtDeclarative)
    PAM

2. Run qmake. You can pass one or more (or none...) of the following variables
to determine, where the things get installed:

<name>      <default value>
prefix      /usr/local
bindir      $(prefix)/bin
sysconfdir  $(prefix)/etc
libdir      $(prefix)/lib
datadir     $(prefix)/share

Example: qmake prefix=/usr sysconfdir=/etc

3. Run make

4. Run make install as root (or sudo make install as normal user).

5. Share and enjoy.
